This twist on the classic manhattan has been a firm favourite since day one at The Sun Tavern, where we use Irish whiskey to give it a much softer tone. Serves 1 35ml Irish whiskey – a good one such as Slane25ml Cocchi Americano10ml Bénédictine1 dash Peychaud’s bitters1 lemon twist, to garnish Fill a glass or jug with ice, add all the ingredients except the garnish and stir to chill. Strain into coupette or martini glass, and serve with a twist of lemon. • Andy Kerr, The Sun Tavern, London E2